SAM can be useful in complex scenes where characters' faces are close to each other and 'BBOX Detector (SEGS)' fails to produce a good result (e.g., a kiss). However, I think it's still better to create a mask manually or refine the mask from SAM before using it. 

To use SAM, connect "Pixelwise(SEGS & MASKS ForEach)" to "SEGS Assign (label)"
digital art,  greyscale, monochrome, game cg, 2D animation, anime, cartoon, 3d art, 3d, mosaic, masking, watermark, signature, sketch, drawing, cartoon

If you get an OOM error, try lowering the tile_batch_size.

An I2R image can be used as a ControlNet reference if matching the original doesn't matter.

nodes.title: Info
widgets_values:
My TensorArt Profile: https://tensor.art/u/794138882072384816

Some character tokens have a strong bias towards their style. In such cases, itâ€™s better to increase character_threshold to 1 to exclude them and/or disable CXH_JoyTag. Alternatively, you can completely disable taggers and use your own prompt.

For general consistency you can use:
    1. LineArt strength
    2. Depth strength
    3. Sampler denoise
    4. Custom prompt
    5. Lora's

For face consistency you can use:
    1. Wildcards
    2. Sampler denoise
    3. Lora's

Ideas for improvement:
    - Improving wildcards 
    - Increasing control in the SEGS node group

Interesting Stuff:
ComfyUI-extension-tutorials: https://github.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-extension-tutorials

Image Comparison & Analysis Tool: https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/geforce/technologies/icat/

Noise before Img2Img: https://www.reddit.com/r/StableDiffusion/comments/1i08k3d/the_difference_from_adding_image_space_noise/

It works unstably, often 2-3 generations are needed to get an OK result. Automatic detection is also not ideal and may require adjustingthe threshold.

If you want to specify a custom wildcard for each eye, hereâ€™s more information about the syntax: https://github.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-extension-tutorials/blob/Main/ComfyUI-Impact-Pack/tutorial/ImpactWildcard.md#special-syntax-for-detailer-wildcard

Example result from this group: https://imgur.com/a/hibG7KA

Main parameters: ControlNet STR, Denoise.

For best results, add a description of the area in the Wildcard Box (e.g., "(hand, fist, gauntlet:1.1)")
